  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-01-13",
    "date": "2022-05-27T13:32:44Z",
    "text": "Save America's Rural Hospitals Act\n\nThis bill establishes and otherwise modifies payment requirements for rural health care providers under Medicare and Medicaid, including by (1) exempting Medicare payments to rural hospitals from sequestration, (2) making permanent certain payment increases for services in rural areas (e.g., Medicaid primary care services), and (3) permanently removing the 96-hour physician certification requirement for inpatient critical access hospital services under Medicare."
  },
